# CSS Selectors ðŸŽ¯

Selectors pattern-match elements.

## 1. Element Selector
Selects all elements of a given type.
```css
p {
  text-align: center;
  color: red;
}
```

## 2. ID Selector
Selects a unique element with a specific `id` attribute using `#`.
```css
#para1 {
  text-align: center;
  color: red;
}
```

## 3. Class Selector
Selects elements with a specific `class` attribute using `.`.
```css
.center {
  text-align: center;
  color: red;
}
```

> ðŸ’¡ **Tip:** ID is unique per page, Class can be used on multiple elements.

# More Selectors ðŸŒŸ

## Universal Selector (*)
Selects all elements on the page.
```css
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}
```

## Grouping Selector
Selects multiple elements with the same style.
```css
h1, h2, p {
  text-align: center;
  color: red;
}
```
